definition.value: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of cinnamic acid.
A beta-D-GlcpN-(1->6)-D-GlcpN in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
